cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on establishing reliable communication infrastructure using unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) for public safety communications (PSC) in a heterogeneous network (HetNet) environment. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 

2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The use of UAVs as unmanned aerial base stations (UABSs) can be considered as a robotics application. 

3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may also touch upon the security aspects of PSC and UAV-assisted communication infrastructure. 

4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper mentions the use of a genetic algorithm for optimizing the locations of UABSs. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence. 

5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may also discuss the control and management of the UAV-assisted communication infrastructure.
